                    "company": "Delft University of Technology",
                    "description": "For this project I have developed my own codes using Matlab for designing and optimization of optical imaging systems. The task of the project was to assess the performance of the Genetic Algorithms (GA) in optimization of optical imaging systems and to find out the influence of GA tuning parameters on the results. To reach the aims, I did write different codes in modelling the optical imaging systems, ray-tracing, optical parameter calculation, optimization and plenty of data analysis. To validate the developed codes the results of all steps have been checked against the commercial lens-design software package Zemax. The results were in high agreement with those of Zemax. Using our developed codes we could provide some guideline on the GAs in lens design field.",
